claim.claim-text:
14. An in vehicle speaker rotational mounting structure comprising:
a speaker unit having a claw portion;
a panel member on which the speaker unit is mounted;
a first slit portion formed in the panel member for insertion of the claw portion;
a second slit portion provided continuously from the first slit portion in a circumferential direction and having an engagement portion where the claw portion and the panel member are brought into engagement with each other; and
a recess provided in a circumference of the speaker unit,
wherein a jig is inserted into the recess so as to rotate the speaker unit therewith from a first position where the claw portion is positioned in the first slit portion to a second position where the claw portion is positioned in the second slit portion to thereby fix the speaker unit to the panel member of the vehicle.
